Beulah COX, Administratrix, v. UNITED STATES of America. No. 1371. Circuit Court of Appeals, Tenth Circuit. Jan. 25, 1936. William A. Tidwell, of Idabel, Old., for appellant. Randolph C. Shaw, Sp. Asst, to Atty. Gen., for the United States.

Before PHILLIPS, McDERMOTT, and BRATTON, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed pursuant to agreement of counsel.
